The paper deals with characterizing points in Euclidean space that lie on computable curves of finite length, which involves concepts from computational geometry (cs.CG) and computability theory (cs.DS). The paper also involves the formulation and proof of a computable extension of the analyst's traveling salesman theorem, which is a result in geometric measure theory and could potentially fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC), logic in computer science (cs.LO), and scientific computing (cs.SC).
